Implementation of North-South Joint Declaration Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 20 (KCNA) -- Political parties and organizations of different countries issued statements on the occasion of the 4th anniversary of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 The Workers' Party, the Communist Party, the Socialist Party, the Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), the National Socialist Party and the Socialist Party of Bangladesh and the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship in a joint statement on June 9 once again called for the implementation of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying four years have passed since the publication of the joint declaration, the statement noted that peace and reunification of Korea, being an important political issue related to peace in Asia and the rest of the world, can be successfully achieved only when the joint declaration is fully implemented. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The National Movement of the Genuine Lumumbist Combatants of Democratic Congo, the Socialist People's Alliance of Democratic Congo, the Democratic Congo-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Association and the Working People's Association of Democratic Congo in a joint statement on June 11 said the change in the relations between the north and the south of Korea is the fruition of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Holding that the joint declaration should be implemented to the letter for the Korean reunification, the statement called for rejecting foreign interference in the Korean issue and demanded the sycophantic and treacherous forces in south Korea halt their anti-reunification acts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Dominican Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification in a statement on June 14 on the occasion of the 4th anniversary of the joint declaration expressed its will to steadily intensify the movement for solidarity with the just cause of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve national reunification.

Joint Concert Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 20 (KCNA) -- A joint concert of the Band of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and vocal soloists of Italy was given at the Mansudae Art Theatre Saturday to mark the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Among the audience were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Jong Ha Chol, officials concerned and creators and artistes in the field of culture and art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also seeing it were Antonino Bevacqua, professor of vocal music at Santa Cecilia State Conservatory of Italy, and his party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The skilful musicians of the band and Italian vocal soloists who are international concours winners put on the stage Korean-and world-famous songs prepared with utmost care to mark the significant day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean musicians impressively presented orchestral music "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il" and "Thunder on Jong Il Peak." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Italian soloists presented male baritone solo, female soprano and other numbers to the accompaniment of the playing of the band. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage was an orchestral music and chorus "Snow Flakes Falling from Nocturnal Sky" performed by the band and the State Merited Chorus of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The concert was acclaimed by the audience for the high artistry, rich emotion, refined rendition skill and well-knit ensemble of the performers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was presented to the performers in congratulation of their successful performance.

Russian Diplomats Help Korean Farmers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Ambassador Andrei Karlov and staff members of the Russian embassy in Pyongyang on June 18 helped members of the DPRK-Russia Friendship Kochang Co-op Farm in Chollima County, South Phyongan Province, in farm work.
 The guests helped farmers in weeding on a maize field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During break, the guests conversed and sang songs with farmers, deepening the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador said that he was glad to work with farmers at the friendship co-op farm when the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the C.C., the WPK is being significantly commemorated and wished the farm success in this year's agricultural production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day staff members of the Russian embassy handed aid materials to the farm.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a floral basket from the Chinese embassy here on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of his start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 It was conveyed to an official concerned by Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters "We warmly congratulate General Secretary Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of your start of work at the Central Committee of the Party". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also conveyed to the official concerned was a gift to Kim Jong Il presented by Wu Donghe.

Internat'l Scientific Symposium on Potato Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- An international scientific symposium on potato was held here from June 16 to 18.
 Present at the symposium were representatives of the DPRK, international organizations and various countries, the resident coordinator of the Federal Department of the Foreign Affairs of Swiss Confederation and members of the missions of international organizations and officials of different embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kye Yong Sam, president of the Academy of Agriculture, in an address at an opening ceremony extended thanks to the Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation of Foreign Affairs and the International Center for Potato Cultivation for having rendered sincere aid and positive support for the success of the symposium and to those organizations and institutions of different countries for having sent scientists and technicians in the field of potato research to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that the symposium would offer an occasion for a wide-range discussion of theoretical and practical issues arising in putting the potato farming on scientific and modern basis, increasing potato production and expanding their application. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyok Jin, vice-minister of Agriculture, at a congratulatory speech referred to the fact that leader Kim Jong Il, with a deep insight into the significance of potato farming, initiated a drive to effect a signal turn in potato farming and has wisely led it, thus bringing about a radical boost in potato cultivation in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the conviction that the symposium would help widely swap advanced scientific and technological achievements and good experience gained by various countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Resident Coordinator Ueli Muller, speaking at the symposium, said that he was pleased with the present remarkable boost in potato cultivation in the DPRK and hoped that the symposium would offer an important occasion for scientific exchange and cooperation in potato cultivation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floor was taken by scientists and researchers from different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A memorandum on the successful symposium was issued then.

Rodong Sinmun on Era of Independence and Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- It is a clear proof of the tremendous vitality of the June 15 joint declaration that the banner of the spirit of "By our nation itself" is fluttering over the land of three thousand-ri and the national reunification movement has been put on the orbit of independence, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article carried in connection with the fact that the historic day, the 4th anniversary of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, was significantly observed.
 Over the last four years during which Koreans have implemented the June 15 joint declaration, they have learned the truth that it is the shortcut to reunification for the Koreans to join efforts and maintained the independent stand to solve the reunification issue through national cooperation without depending on others, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The period since the adoption of the June 15 joint declaration witnessed multi-channeled talks between the authorities in the north and the south including more than 10 rounds of ministerial talks. There have been wide-range dialogues and contacts between personages from all walks of life and organizations in the north and the south and overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All those dialogues and contacts were aimed at solving the reunification issue by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation, free from outside domination and interference, and have been true to the principle of placing the common interests of the nation above all and subordinating everything to national reunification, not allowing anyone to seek a sinister political purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The era of independence and reunification calling for the realization of national sovereignty has advanced amid a fierce struggle against the U.S. keen to infringe upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation's movement for national reunification has definitely turned into a nation-wide movement as all Koreans, be they authorities or common people, have made joint efforts irrespective of idea, political view and religious belief. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Brisk are cooperation and exchange between the north and the south in different fields in the main spirit of the June 15 joint declaration  The era of independence and reunification ushered in by the June 15 joint declaration clearly taught the Koreans the truth of independence and unity and powerfully aroused them to the patriotic struggle for reunification, thus recording the history of the reunification movement with events and miracles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All these shining successes made in the period of implementing the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration are the precious fruition of the great patriotic Songun politics of leader  Kim Jong Il, a peerless patriot and illustrious commander born of Heaven, and the tireless patriotic guidance provided by him to the reunification movement.

Celebration Meetings Held in Local Areas and at KPA Units
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in all provinces, cities and counties across the country and at units of the three services of the Korean People's Army (KPA) on Friday to celebrate the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
 The reporters at the meetings referred to the immortal exploits performed by Kim Jong Il who has set a brilliant example in building a revolutionary party with his outstanding idea and leadership despite all challenges of history for the last 40 years in the nearly 60 year-long glorious history of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He formulated President Kim Il Sung's revolutionary idea as an integral system of the idea, theory and method of Juche and declared it as the guiding idea of the revolution in the present times, they noted, adding that on this basis, he unrolled the programme for modeling the whole society on the Juche idea, thereby perfectly settling the issue of the guiding idea and supreme programme of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went on: Kim Jong Il laid down the WPK's traditional benevolent politics, politics of love and trust, as a socialist political mode and has successfully enforced it. He has thus successfully achieved the single-hearted unity of the leader, the Party and the popular masses and led the WPK to strictly abide by the basic principles governing the revolutionary party construction in its activities to develop the Party into an invincible socialist ruling party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attaching great importance to realizing the integration of the Party and the army, he has firmly established the unitary leadership system of the Party in the KPA under the banner of modeling the whole army on the Juche idea and thus turned the KPA into the leader's army and the Party's army, making the Party and the army an integral whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set out the Songun policy to cope with the grave situation the Korean revolution faced in the 1990s of the last century and has developed the WPK to be a revolutionary party in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to Kim Jong Il's wise leadership over the WPK the DPRK has won one victory after another in the fierce struggle against the imperialists and the U.S. and has reached a high watermark of prosperity through a grand onward movement to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on all the Party members, servicepersons and people to strengthen the WPK under the banner of the great Songun policy in order to pave a wide avenue for fresh success in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, bring earlier the independent reunification of the country and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche.

DPRK Introduced by Foreign Internet
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The DPRK was introduced by Internet on a world-wide scale.
 A number of independent and progressive parties, organizations, institutions and public figures in foreign countries including Belgium, Peru, Spain, Poland, Italy and the Czech Republic carried in internet homepages materials showing the wise leadership, immortal exploits and noble virtues of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il, and documents, photos, films and other information introducing the true feature of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Belgian Labour Party, the Communist Party of Peru (Red Motherland) and the Peruvian newspaper "Nuestra bandera" edited articles titled "Kim Il Sung decorating the 20th Century" and "Kim Jong Il, unique political mode".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Association for Friendship with the Korean People in Spain edited photos and articles introducing the DPRK and posted the Korean documentary films in Internet homepage consisting of six chapters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage "Juche", specialized in introducing the Juche Idea, was opened by the Italian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage consists of three chapters including "The Democratic People's Republic of Korea" and "Information" under the title "Korea is one !" against the background of a picture of the world progressive people holding aloft the torch of Juche. It introduces the history, the Juche Idea, reunification, landscape, health care, education and other sectors of the DPRK and carries photos and explanatory notes on the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Monument to Party Founding, the Chollima Statue, the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre and other monumental edifices. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great number of associations, groups and clubs in Britain, the U.S., Jordan and other countries introduced the DPRK and conducted solidarity activities through Internet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year the British Society for the Study of Songun Politics carried photos showing the revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Il, pictures Kim Il Sung had taken with Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war woman hero, photos showing the invincible might of the Korean People's Army and articles titled "Glorious Supreme Commander of the People" and "Kim Jong Suk, woman general of Mt. Paektu" on the occasion of her birthday (Dec 24). In April this year it carried a special write-up of photos and articles showing the revolutionary history and exploits of Kim Il Sung under the title "Generalissimo Kim Il Sung Is the Eternal Red Sun of Juche". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the beginning of this year, the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics established homepage titled "The Room for the Study of the Red Sun of Militant Socialism of Juche" and screened pictures of Kim Il Sung had taken with Kim Jong Il and edited more than 100 wise sayings of Kim Jong Il in booklet and introduced the articles on his greatness in over 30 progressive websites in the U.S. and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In February and April the group opened "A special commemoration page of Kim Jong Il" and edited more than 100 propositions from Kim Il Sung's reminiscences "With the Century" and his brief biography, Kim Jong Il's famous works and propositions, articles headlined "President Kim Il Sung, the Eternal Sun" and "Ever Shining Exploit of the President" and e-book "Question and Answer on the Juche Idea".

Russian Dance Company Gives Performances in Wonsan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wonsan, June 18 (KCNA) -- The visiting State Academic Moiseyev Folk Dance Company of Russia gave performances in Wonsan on June 17 and 18.
 It was appreciated by Ko Jong Dok, chairman of the Kangwon Provincial People's Committee, Ju Kyong Jun, secretary of the Kangwon Provincial Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, and working people from all walks of life in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company raised curtain with the approach of significant June 19 and put on the stage colorful numbers they prepared with sincerity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dances including "Guerrillas" and "Summer" reflecting the heroic trait and patriotic spirit of the Soviet people displayed in the just struggle against fascism during the Great Patriotic War were acclaimed by the audience for the high ideological value and wonderful artistic skill of the performers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They put on the stages folk dances of different countries as well as the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performances ended with a chorus representing the friendly relations between the DPRK and Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets were conveyed to the performers in congratulation of their successful performances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Performance continues.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from NDFSK Central Committee
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a letter from the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of south Korea Saturday on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of his start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 During the past four decades you have led the WPK along the only road of victory and performed immortal exploits with the most outstanding leadership in the world, reflecting the need of the times and the desire of the people, the letter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You, endowed with gifted wisdom, have glorified the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung as the only idea guiding the era of independence through your energetic ideological and theoretical activities. This has been recorded as a remarkably great exploit in strengthening and developing the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK has converted the north into an ideologically, politically and militarily strong power and won one victory after another in fierce confrontation with the U.S. and stood in the spotlight of the world as a conning tower defending the peace and stability of the world on the anti-imperialist and military forefront. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These results have been possible thanks to you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter noted that as Kim Jong Il brought about a signal turn in the movement for national reunification true to the noble intention of President Kim Il Sung, reconciliation, unity, cooperation and exchange between the south and the north have gained momentum under the banner of "By our nation itself" and a new era of independence and reunification dawned in the wake of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration in which the song "We Are One" is reverberating far and wide in the land of three thousand-ri. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, upholding the June 15 joint declaration, a landmark for reunification in the new century provided by you, will resolutely foil the U.S. imperialists' vicious anti-north and anti-reunification moves through national cooperation against the U.S., make 2005, 60 years since the national division, the year the U.S. colonial domination and its occupation of south Korea are terminated and bring earlier the dawn of a reunified country when all the Koreans will live as one in the independent and democratic new society, the letter concluded.

DPRK FM Spokesman Refutes U.S. Much Ado about "Flesh Traffic"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry Saturday gave an answer to a question put by KCNA as regards the U.S. renewed accusation against the DPRK over the "issue of flesh traffic."
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Department of State in a "report on flesh traffic" on June 14 dealt with "flesh traffic" in at least 130 countries as it pleased. In the report it malignantly slandered the DPRK, absurdly asserting that it is a "source of flesh traffic" and "it does not have even the lowest standard for combating flesh traffic". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is nothing but a sheer fabrication as it is stereotyped sophism the U.S. used every year to pull up the independent countries which refuse to meekly obey it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Flesh traffic, in fact, originated from the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an undeniable historical fact that the U.S. is a rouge state as it exterminated many Indians and got rich through slave trade and other flesh traffic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is repeating this blood-stained history. It is ill-famed for being a barren land of human rights in the 21st century as it is committing genocide of contemporary form in different parts of the world including Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is behaving as if it were a world human rights judge, oblivious of its miserable situation where it is under world curse and fire for being a kingpin of mass killings and human rights abuses. This is nothing but a scoff of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should know that such a thing as "flesh traffic" can never exist in the DPRK in the light of the nature of the Korean-style socialist system based on the man-centred Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The desperate efforts on the part of the Bush administration to tarnish the image of the DPRK and internationally isolate and stifle it will only harden the will of the army and people of the DPRK to firmly defend the socialist system.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Performance Given by Wangjaesan Light Music Band
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA)-- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, enjoyed a performance given by the Wangjaesan Light Music Band.
 Among the audience were Kim Yong Chun, chief of the General Staff of the Korean People's Army, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, and other senior officials of the Party and the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The band put on the stage a concert to the accompaniment of a trumpet "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee," an instrumental music and song "Song of Victory in Battle Resounding Forth in Forest," a female vocal solo and Pangchang "Visit to Post at Dawn," a female group dance "Winnow Dance," a folk dance "Trio Dance" and other colorful numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang in high praises of the laudable exploits performed by the heroic KPA and people in the crucible of the nearly half century-long struggle, true to the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also truthfully represented the high national pride, self-respect and infinite happiness of the servicepersons and people who lead a worthwhile life, having him at the top post of the Party, the army and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance deeply impressed the audience as it reflected the high spirit of the army and people dynamically advancing to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied with the successful performance given by the creators and artistes of the band with high artistry. He called on them to positively contribute to the revolutionary education of the Party members and other working people through revolutionary and militant art activities in the future, too.
